The large number of combinations available from a small number of keys allows text or commands to be entered with one hand, leaving the other hand free to do something else.
Most keyloggers can be fooled by  alternating between typing the login credentials and typing characters somewhere else in the focus windowhttp://cups.cs.cmu.edu/soups/2006/posters/herley-poster_abstract.pdf .
The use of any keyboard may cause serious injury (that is, carpal tunnel syndrome or other repetitive strain injury) to hands, wrists, arms, neck or back.
